# {{.WorkspaceName}} Workspace Development Skill

This is the workspace entry skill. It only decides task ownership, selects child project skills, and identifies when cross-project rules apply. Child project architecture, coding conventions, business methods, and executable rules must be read from the affected child project skill before implementation decisions.

## Usage

1. Read [Workspace Overview](./references/workspace-overview.md) first; use its routing table to confirm path ownership, child skill locations, and the default write boundary.
2. For a single child project task, enter only that child project's `SKILL.md` and `references/project-spec.md`; do not read or edit other child projects as a side effect.
3. For contracts, shared code, infrastructure, root scripts, or multi-child tasks, read [Cross-Project Rules](./references/cross-project-rules.md) before choosing the execution order.
{{if .WorkflowReferences}}4. When a stored workspace workflow matches the task, read that workflow first, then execute with the overview and cross-project rules.
5. If the overview, child skill, workflow, or config cannot confirm product boundaries, project responsibility, delivery model, validation commands, or cross-project dependencies, ask the user instead of inventing details.
